    // Accessibility statement page
    stmt_back: 'Back to Home',
    stmt_body: '<p class="statement-intro"><strong>SHINE</strong> — Measurement, Drawing &amp; 3D Visualization Services — is committed to making the website accessible to all people, including those with disabilities. We work continuously to improve site accessibility and compliance with required standards.</p><h2>What is web accessibility?</h2><p>An accessible website enables people with disabilities to browse it with the same level of efficiency and enjoyment as other users, through assistive technologies and appropriate site design.</p><h2>Accessibility Adaptations on the Site</h2><p>The site has been adapted in accordance with the Israeli standard (SI 5568) and WCAG 2.1 guidelines at level AA. Adaptations include, among others:</p><h3>Keyboard Usage</h3><ul><li>The site can be navigated using keyboard only, without a mouse</li><li>All functions are available via keyboard</li><li>The tab order on the site is logical and follows the page structure</li><li>Interactive elements (buttons, links) have clear focus indicators</li></ul><h3>Assistive Technology Support</h3><ul><li>The site supports leading screen readers such as NVDA, JAWS and VoiceOver</li><li>The use of ARIA tags enables correct understanding of structure and content</li><li>All images include descriptive alternative text (Alt Text)</li><li>Headings are clearly marked in hierarchical order (H1, H2, H3...)</li></ul><h3>Accessibility Menu</h3><p>The site includes a dedicated accessibility menu that allows:</p><ul><li><strong>Text enlargement</strong> — increasing the font size on the site</li><li><strong>Text reduction</strong> — decreasing the font size on the site</li><li><strong>High contrast</strong> — switching site colors to maximum contrast</li><li><strong>Reset settings</strong> — returning all settings to default</li></ul><p>Settings are saved automatically and loaded on your next visit to the site.</p><h3>Colors and Contrast</h3><ul><li>Color contrast between text and background meets the required standard</li><li>The site does not rely on color alone to convey information</li><li>Option to switch to high contrast mode</li></ul><h3>Multilingual and Bidirectional Text Support</h3><ul><li>The site supports multiple languages with correct text directionality (RTL for Hebrew/Arabic, LTR for others)</li><li>Texts are aligned correctly per language</li><li>All site components are adapted for multilingual browsing</li></ul><h3>Responsive Design</h3><ul><li>The site is adapted for viewing on various devices — desktop, tablet and smartphone</li><li>Content reorganizes automatically according to screen size</li><li>All functions are available on the mobile version as well</li></ul><h2>Browsers and Compatibility</h2><p>The site has been tested and found to work correctly in the following browsers:</p><ul><li>Google Chrome (latest versions)</li><li>Mozilla Firefox (latest versions)</li><li>Safari (latest versions)</li><li>Microsoft Edge (latest versions)</li></ul><h2>Known Limitations</h2><p>Despite our efforts to make all pages on the site accessible, some content may not yet be fully accessible. We continue our efforts to improve site accessibility over time.</p><div class="contact-box"><h3>Encountered an accessibility issue on the site?</h3><p>We do everything in our power to maintain accessibility standards. If you encounter a problem, we would appreciate it if you would contact us and we will do our best to address it promptly.</p><p><strong>Contact methods:</strong></p><ul><li>Phone: <a href="tel:+972523386911" dir="ltr">052-338-6911</a></li><li>Email: <a href="mailto:shine.measur@gmail.com">shine.measur@gmail.com</a></li><li>WhatsApp: <a href="https://wa.me/972523386911" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Send a message</a></li></ul></div><h2>Accessibility Coordinator</h2><p><strong>Name:</strong> Shani Akuka — SHINE<br><strong>Phone:</strong> <a href="tel:+972523386911" dir="ltr">052-338-6911</a><br><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:shine.measur@gmail.com">shine.measur@gmail.com</a></p><h2>Supervision and Enforcement</h2><p>The party responsible for enforcing the Equal Rights for Persons with Disabilities Regulations (Accessibility Adjustments to Service), 5773-2013, is the Commissioner for Equal Rights of Persons with Disabilities at the Ministry of Justice.</p><p><strong>Ministry of Justice — Commissioner for Equal Rights of Persons with Disabilities:</strong><br>Phone: 02-5318558<br><a href="https://www.gov.il/he/departments/the_commissioner_for_equal_rights_of_persons_with_disabilities" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Commissioner for Equal Rights website</a></p><p class="update-date">This accessibility statement was last updated: January 2026</p>',

